    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Tibial tray contact stress sensitivity analysis — material and geometry parameters",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analysis was performed varying UHMWPE elastic modulus (±15%), tibial baseplate thickness (±1 mm), and femoral condyle radius (±0.5 mm) across the five physiological loading scenarios. Peak contact stress exhibited greatest sensitivity to UHMWPE modulus (normalized sensitivity index 0.62), with geometry parameters contributing less than 18% of total output variance; these findings informed the uncertainty bounds applied in the validation comparison and confirmed that modulus characterisation is the dominant source of model output uncertainty."
  },
